threepio.tabler.container
Class Cell<E>

java.lang.Object
  threepio.tabler.container.Cell<E>
Direct Known Subclasses:
StringCell
public abstract class Cell<E>
extends java.lang.Object

A Cell is a cell of a table. It is where the "live" parts of the table happen, such as "knowing" if the data was changed, or was inserted.

Author:
jhoule

public void silentSet(E it)
Sets without modifying anything but the data. USING THIS CAN BREAK THE "SELF-AWARE" PART OF CELLS. This method is intended ONLY for "invisible" modifications, such as creating anchors and links.
